	<section id="command.ref.normalise"><title>normalise</title>
		<indexterm><primary>commands</primary><secondary>normalise</secondary></indexterm>
		<para><emphasis>Syntax:</emphasis></para>
		<itemizedlist>
			<listitem>
				<para> double normalise ( vector v )</para>
			</listitem>
		</itemizedlist>
		<para>Normalises the vector ''v'', returning the magnitude of the vector before the normalisation was performed.</para>
	
		<para>For example:</para>
		<synopsis>
			vector v = { 1, 2, 3 };
			double mag = normalise(v);
			printf(&quot;Normalised vector is { %f, %f, %f }, old magnitude was %f\n&quot;, v.x, v.y, v.z, mag);
		</synopsis>
		<para>prints the following:</para>
		<synopsis>
			Normalised vector is { 0.267261, 0.534522, 0.801784 }, old magnitude was 3.741657
		</synopsis>
	
	</section>
	
